org.apache.flink.api.common.typeutils

接口 TypeDeserializer<T>

  • 类型参数:
    T - The data type that the deserializer deserializes.
    所有已知实现类:
    TypeDeserializerAdapter

    public interface TypeDeserializer<T>
    This interface describes the methods that are required for a data type to be read by the Flink runtime. Specifically, this interface contains the deserialization methods. In contrast, the TypeSerializer interface contains the complete set of methods for both serialization and deserialization.

    The methods in this class are assumed to be stateless, such that it is effectively thread safe. Stateful implementations of the methods may lead to unpredictable side effects and will compromise both stability and correctness of the program.

    • 方法详细资料

      • duplicate

        TypeSerializer<T> duplicate()
        Creates a deep copy of this deserializer if it is necessary, i.e. if it is stateful. This can return itself if the serializer is not stateful. We need this because deserializers might be used in several threads. Stateless deserializers are inherently thread-safe while stateful deserializers might not be thread-safe.

      • deserialize

        T deserialize(DataInputView source)
       throws java.io.IOException
        De-serializes a record from the given source input view.
        参数:
        source - The input view from which to read the data.
        返回:
        The deserialized element.
        抛出:
        java.io.IOException - Thrown, if the de-serialization encountered an I/O related error. Typically raised by the input view, which may have an underlying I/O channel from which it reads.

      • deserialize

        T deserialize(T reuse,
              DataInputView source)
       throws java.io.IOException
        De-serializes a record from the given source input view into the given reuse record instance if mutable.
        参数:
        reuse - The record instance into which to de-serialize the data.
        source - The input view from which to read the data.
        返回:
        The deserialized element.
        抛出:
        java.io.IOException - Thrown, if the de-serialization encountered an I/O related error. Typically raised by the input view, which may have an underlying I/O channel from which it reads.
